            "answer_text": "Hmm, well an angry moment I've witnessed from him was in one of the days of his trial. A reporter pushed a fan on the ground to get a picture of Michael and was really getting on his nerves. Than Michael started yelling to this guy and said \"Fuck you\":  His sister Janet was also pretty angry and so seemed his mother. Anyway, with all what was going on, I understand him perfectly well. And of course, as a human, he would get angry at other moments, but I think, in no way was he dangerous when he did that. It's just like anybody who would get angry. I very rarely do that as well and most of the time, I manage not to show it, there are times when I can't help it and still, I react as easy as I can, with some sarcasm and a higher tone, but not yelling and breaking things around. Some day I may do it if I go on like this, who knows... Anyway, that's something pretty human, we all have it and he had it as well. ",
